    <text id="B0168T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Brackett writes about the administration of a local school.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient"><abbr expan="Thomas">Tho.</abbr> P. Jackson<lb/>Staunton<abbr expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr></name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1867-11-18"><abbr expan="November">Nov.</abbr> 18, 1867</date>
                        <name type="place">Harpers Ferry, <abbr expan="West Virginia">W.Va.</abbr></name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Dear Sir:</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I am surprised to find that your letter is dated so far back as <abbr
                        expan="October">Oct.</abbr> 19. I suppose Mr. Scott is at Staunton, so you
                    are relieved of the immediate charge of the school. If Mr. Scott uses the
                    articles you purchased in <orig reg="connection">connexion</orig> with his
                    school. I am certain that the <abbr expan="African Methodist Association"
                    >A.M.A.</abbr> will pay for them. <del hand="h1">If</del> I think the National
                    will do the same. I hope <unclear>she</unclear> in Staunton in two or three
                    weeks. I hope the school is prospering, and the "School house" under way.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Yours &amp;c.</salute>
                    <signed>N. C. Brackett</signed>
                    <seg type="postscript">Please take my book from this office and take are
                            <unclear>fit</unclear> I will assist you if I can do anything, in
                            <unclear>petty</unclear> poor money back, when I get to Staunton.
                    N.C.B.</seg>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
